: The regional competitions of the Naipunyam Skill Fiesta, organised by the Kerala Academy for Skill Excellence in association with the Department for Industrial Training, will begin at the Government ITI in Kozhikode on Monday.Minister for Social Justice and Panchayats M.K. Muneer will inaugurate the festival while A.. Pradeep Kumar, MLA, will preside over the function.M.K. Raghavan, MP will be the chief guest on the occasion.Candidates from Malappuram, Kannur, Kasaragod, Wayanad and Kozhikode districts will take part in the competitions on various trades.The fiesta will be on till January 11. Competitions will be held in 12 trades. Competitions in welding, plumbing, fitter, electrical, carpentry and automobile technology will be held at the Government ITI in Kozhikode while those in fashion technology, electronics, mobile robotics and Autocad will be held at the Government Womenâ€™s ITI in Kozhikode. Competitions in Catering and Restaurant Services as well as Bakery and Confectionary will be held at the Government ITI at Kalpetta, Wayanad.